<div id="pf4610" class="pf w53 h2f7" data-page-no="4610"><div class="pc pc4610 w53 h2f7"><div class="t m86a x81 h5 y2f71 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">LESSON 3 July 13-19 </div><div class="t m268 xd6 h109 y2caa ff4 fs40 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3 Thc2 Fin</div><div class="t m6a0 x8b h1ed y2caa ff2 fs40 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">-</div><div class="t m4895 x9e h1e7 y2ce1 ff2 fsc fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Et </div><div class="t m124f x5a h109 y2ce1 ff4 fs40 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">IDIFIE5cog </div><div class="t m837 xb4 h5 y2a99 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;How should man be just with </div><div class="t mdff xd6 h5 y2bbb ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">sod?&quot; (Job 9:2). </div><div class="t mf6e xb4 h35 y295c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">This is probably the most </div><div class="t mf1d xd6 h35 y243d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">penetrating question raised in the </div><div class="t m1be xd6 h35 y238f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">section under study in this </div><div class="t m248 xd6 h35 y44e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lessonâ€”Job 3 through 11. These </div><div class="t m433 xd6 h35 yd18 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapters include six speeches: Job </div><div class="t m7ca xd6 h35 y9cb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(3:1-26), Eliphaz (4:1 through 5:27), </div><div class="t mb65 xd6 h35 y204c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job 6:1 through 7:21), Bildad (8:1-22), </div><div class="t m882 xd6 h35 y2af ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job (9:1 through 10:22), Zophar </div><div class="t m853 xd6 h35 y23f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(11:1-20). These speeches represent </div><div class="t ma6 xd6 h35 y4fa ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the first of three dialogues or cycles </div><div class="t me7b xd6 h35 y1034 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that continue through the thirty-first </div><div class="t m234 xd6 h35 y1f1 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">chapter. </div><div class="t mae1 xb4 h35 y4f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">It should be pointed out that many </div><div class="t m620 xd5 h35 y4fd ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expositors begin the first dialogue </div><div class="t ma02 xd6 h35 y60f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">with chapter four and continue it </div><div class="t ma11 xd5 h35 ye74 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">through chapter fourteen. The writer </div><div class="t m8c xd6 h35 y436 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">of these lessons feels that each </div><div class="t m105c xd5 h35 y29e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">dialogue or cycle begins with a speech </div><div class="t ma6c xd5 h35 ydb ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">by Job rather than with a speech by </div><div class="t m9db xd6 h35 y8d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Efiphaz. This is the structure followed </div><div class="t m1323 xd5 h35 y918 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">in the </div><div class="t m6d4 x3e h35 y918 ff5 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">S.D.A. Bible Commentary. </div><div class="t m6c7 xd5 h35 y214 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">However, this is a matter of opinion </div><div class="t m6ab xd5 h35 y496 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and does not affect the message of the </div><div class="t mdd6 xd5 h35 y147f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">book. </div><div class="t m736 xda h35 y405 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job 3, as pointed out in part 6 of </div><div class="t maf0 xd5 h35 y158 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson 2, begins with a passage </div><div class="t m826 xd5 h35 y450 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">reflecting gloom and darkness. Job  </div><div class="t m186 x1f h35 y2b2d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">curses the day he was born. He longs </div><div class="t md06 x1f h35 y2b82 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">for the grave: &quot;There the wicked cease </div><div class="t mace x1f h35 y2c64 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">from troubling; and there the weary </div><div class="t mdcb x1f h35 y295c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">be at rest. There the prisoners rest </div><div class="t m116f x1f h35 y243d ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">together; they hear not the voice of </div><div class="t m17d x1f h35 y238f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the oppressor. The small and great are </div><div class="t me7a x1f h35 y2017 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">there; and the servant is free from his </div><div class="t m233 x1f h35 yd18 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">master. Wherefore is light given to </div><div class="t m44f x1f h35 y5f6 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">him that is in misery, and life unto the </div><div class="t m973 x1f h35 yf16 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">bitter in soul; which long for death, </div><div class="t m1344 x1f h35 y2af ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">but it cometh not; and dig for it more </div><div class="t m41a x1f h35 y23f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">than for hid treasures; which rejoice </div><div class="t m844 x1f h35 y4fa ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">exceedingly, and are glad, when they </div><div class="t m845 x1f h35 y1034 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">can find the grave&quot; (verses 17-22). </div><div class="t m9db x1c h35 y778 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The final verses of this sad chapter </div><div class="t mdcb x1f h35 y4f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">are well rendered in the TEV: </div><div class="t m3b6 x1c h35 yae ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">&quot;Instead of eating, I mourn, </div><div class="t m1c4 x56 h35 y413 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and I can never stop groaning. </div><div class="t m70d x1c h35 ye74 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Everything I fear and dread comes </div><div class="t mf16 x78 h35 y436 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">true. </div><div class="t m495 x1c h35 y29e ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">I have no peace, no rest, </div><div class="t m2ac x56 h35 y335 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">and my troubles never end&quot; </div><div class="t m486 x78 h35 ycc9 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(verses 24-26). </div><div class="t m817 x1c h35 y8f7 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The dialogue begins with this </div><div class="t m8fb x1f h35 y8 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">expression of discouragement </div><div class="t m591 x1f h35 y206b ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">including the entire third chapter. It is </div><div class="t m9b1 x1f h35 y147f ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">to this melancholy complaint that </div><div class="t m3be x1f h35 y105 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Eliphaz responds in chapters four and </div><div class="t m49c x1f h35 y998 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">five. </div><div class="t m7ba x1c h35 y450 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">The limits of our Sabbath School </div><div class="t m6d2 x1f h35 y41c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">lesson make it impossible to cover </div><div class="t ma3f x1f h35 y9ad ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">every verse. Selections are made in an </div><div class="t m247 x1f h35 y1074 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">endeavor to recapture the basic </div><div class="t m23f x72 h35 y4ce ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">message of Job. It is urged that each </div><div class="t m54f x72 h35 y6a ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">student of these lessons read the </div><div class="t m658 x72 h35 y80c ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">entire passage, including the verses </div><div class="t m17b x72 h35 y9d3 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">that are not specifically dealt with in </div><div class="t m424 x72 h35 y14 ff2 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">the lessons. </div><div class="t m396 x72 h5 y357 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">DAILY HIGHLIGHTS </div><div class="t m23f x72 h5 y9e8 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">1. </div><div class="t m99 xbc h5 y6f4 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">A Wrong Answer </div><div class="t m66b xbc h5 yd34 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 4:7-9) </div><div class="t m558 x72 h5 y326 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">2. </div><div class="t mdc xbc h5 y326 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">False Friends </div><div class="t m687 xbc h5 yba5 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 6:15-21) </div><div class="t mb7 x72 h5 y2ac ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">3. </div><div class="t me3e xbc h5 y2ac ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Job Challenges God </div><div class="t m5b1 xbc h5 y42b ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 7:19-21)</div><div class="t m4896 x44 h5 y9f ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">- </div><div class="t mf8b xb2 h5 y9f ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0"> </div><div class="t m1ce x72 h5 y343 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">4. </div><div class="t m599 xbc h5 y343 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Ancient Tradition Defended </div><div class="t m5b1 xbc h5 y115 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 8:11-13) </div><div class="t m8a8 x72 h5 yc9 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">5. </div><div class="t ma3b xbc h5 yc9 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">God&apos;s Power and Job&apos;s Weakness </div><div class="t m1e9 xbc h5 y884 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 9:19, 20) </div><div class="t m2ef x8f h5 y5e9 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">6. </div><div class="t m268 xbc h5 y5e9 ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">Repentance Urged </div><div class="t mdf xbc h5 y35c ff3 fs3 fc0 sc0 ls0 ws0">(Job 11:13, 14) </div></div><div class="pi" data-data='{"ctm":[1.000000,0.000000,0.000000,1.000000,0.000000,0.000000]}'></div></div>
